Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with extensions of monadic second-order logic and their expressiveness over finite structures. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper discusses the relative strengths of two logic extensions. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are possible categories as the paper deals with mathematical concepts and structures. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a possible category as the paper deals with the expressiveness of logic extensions in defining languages over finite structures.
